{{! This will be your default layout for all handlebars file rendered. This will be inherited by all other templates. }}
{{! Refer lecture code to learn more on how this works
don't forget to include your css and your client-side script file references in the layout.
for the theme, you can simply read the themePreference for the user and inject it into the body element}}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="UTF-8">
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="/public/css/sitestyles.css">
    </head>
    <body style="background-color: {{#if themePreference}}{{themePreference.backgroundColor}}{{else}}white{{/if}}; color: {{#if themePreference}}{{themePreference.fontColor}}{{else}}black{{/if}};">
        {{{body}}}
    </body>
    <script src="/public/js/form_validate.js"></script>
</html>